    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the overall body of evidence supports a High assurance level. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The test samples factor achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3, but the team judged this shortfall to be offset by the favorable E/uval metrics across all three QoIs, the multi-laboratory test program, and the direct relevance of the validation activities to the COU. The FEA modeling framework is accepted for use in the regulatory submission.",
